In a meeting with leaders of the Congressional Hispanic Caucus, President Obama discussed the options for immigration reform facing Congress. He expressed gratitude for their efforts and emphasized the importance of passing the DREAM Act, which would provide a path to citizenship for young people brought to the US as minors. The President also called for bipartisan support for comprehensive immigration reform and urged Republicans to work with Democrats to address the broken immigration system. He emphasized the need for both parties to work together to tackle the challenges facing the nation.